1
00:00:01,220 --> 00:01:44,050
♪

2
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:59,180
♪

3
00:01:59,180 --> 00:02:01,030
(grunts)

4
00:02:01,030 --> 00:02:07,200
♪

5
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:10,030
So much of warfare
fought in modern times

6
00:02:10,030 --> 00:02:12,200
depends on who has the
greater number of troops.

7
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:14,160
This is decidedly different.

8
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:17,240
I love the feel of
battling one on one.

9
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:20,150
Meldars' master plan
is to take over the world.

10
00:02:20,150 --> 00:02:21,190
He fancies
himself to be

11
00:02:21,190 --> 00:02:23,190
the chivalrous
knight battling me,

12
00:02:23,190 --> 00:02:25,020
who he sees
as inferior.

13
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:28,190
I must stop him,
no matter what the cost.

14
00:02:28,190 --> 00:02:29,190
(grunts)

15
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:34,030
♪

16
00:02:34,030 --> 00:02:35,080
He got him!

17
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:37,170
Come on, Kenshin, don't
let him get away with that!

18
00:02:37,170 --> 00:02:39,120
Lay some Kuzurysen
on that jerk!

19
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:40,190
It's impossible.

20
00:02:40,190 --> 00:02:43,180
With him up on horseback,
it's just not that easy.

21
00:02:43,180 --> 00:02:45,100
Even with Kenshin's
leaping ability,

22
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:48,000
he can't get above Meldars
to deliver a killer blow.

23
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,190
As the Mongols
taught the Chinese,

24
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:51,090
you have to kill
the horse first.

25
00:02:51,090 --> 00:02:52,260
That's how to
bring a rider down.

26
00:02:52,260 --> 00:02:55,070
Kenshin can stop an
attacker on horseback,

27
00:02:55,070 --> 00:02:57,240
but we've never seen
anyone ride like this.

28
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:59,080
♪

29
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:01,190
(horse neighs)

30
00:03:01,190 --> 00:03:03,070
The way they move,
it's as though Meldars

31
00:03:03,070 --> 00:03:04,210
and the horse
are one being.

32
00:03:04,210 --> 00:03:06,050
That's true.

33
00:03:06,050 --> 00:03:08,020
Besides, Kenshin's used
to fighting samurais

34
00:03:08,020 --> 00:03:11,220
with short swords, not a knight
with a long jousting pole.

35
00:03:11,220 --> 00:03:13,150
Are you saying he
hasn't got a chance?

36
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:16,140
♪

37
00:03:16,140 --> 00:03:18,150
Simple physics of
him being on that horse

38
00:03:18,150 --> 00:03:21,120
adds too much energy
to his every move.

39
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,170
(grunts)

40
00:03:22,170 --> 00:03:24,210
If I don't get in closer
and take out his horse,

41
00:03:24,210 --> 00:03:26,010
I haven't got a chance.

42
00:03:26,010 --> 00:03:29,160
(grunting)

43
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:31,020
(yells)

44
00:03:36,210 --> 00:03:38,010
Looks like
even Battosai

45
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:40,080
can't give Meldars
a good challenge.

46
00:03:43,210 --> 00:03:48,000
(groaning)

47
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,060
So, Battosai, is
that the best effort

48
00:03:51,060 --> 00:03:53,210
the Japanese can muster?

49
00:03:53,210 --> 00:03:54,270
You talk a good game,

50
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:57,240
but I don't think
you can deliver.

51
00:03:57,240 --> 00:04:00,080
(groaning)

52
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,230
There's no edge
on his sword.

53
00:04:01,230 --> 00:04:02,280
He can't win.

54
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:04,220
You don't know
much about Kenshin.

55
00:04:04,220 --> 00:04:07,160
I do know a reverse edge
sword is useless in battle.

56
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:09,060
You can't kill
with that sword.

57
00:04:09,060 --> 00:04:10,160
That's why he's
got that sword.

58
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:12,230
He stopped killing
people a long time ago.

59
00:04:12,230 --> 00:04:16,050
He's not a slasher anymore,
but he'll find a way to win.

60
00:04:16,050 --> 00:04:17,170
Huh?

61
00:04:17,170 --> 00:04:19,080
He is trying to
protect people,

62
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:23,040
not bend other people
to his will like you are!

63
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,280
Ha, from his looks
he'll be lucky

64
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:26,240
if he can protect himself.

65
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:27,280
No one can stop me,

66
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:29,160
and once I get a
hold of the medicine

67
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:31,120
I'll be invincible.

68
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:33,290
The Black Knights
will soon rule the world.

69
00:04:33,290 --> 00:04:35,250
A new world,
a new world order

70
00:04:35,250 --> 00:04:37,130
where we will
bury your kind.

71
00:04:37,130 --> 00:04:40,130
This new world order of
yours will only promote hate.

72
00:04:40,130 --> 00:04:42,120
Any new world order
should foster peace,

73
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:44,200
acceptance
and understanding.

74
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,080
You must be stopped
or innocent people

75
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:48,180
will have their lives
snuffed out by your mob.

76
00:04:48,180 --> 00:04:50,260
And you can't stop it!

77
00:04:50,260 --> 00:04:53,060
I will stop you
with all that I have.

78
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:54,110
I'm ready!

79
00:04:54,110 --> 00:05:00,020
♪

80
00:05:00,020 --> 00:05:02,120
So, you're ready, huh?

81
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:05,020
(laughing sinisterly)

82
00:05:05,020 --> 00:05:11,120
♪

83
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:14,110
I must kill you,
you oriental monkey!

84
00:05:14,110 --> 00:05:19,020
♪

85
00:05:19,020 --> 00:05:20,210
You and your people
have no sense

86
00:05:20,210 --> 00:05:22,260
of the history of the
Order of the Black Knights

87
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:24,230
and how through the
ages we have perfected

88
00:05:24,230 --> 00:05:26,280
our techniques for warfare.

89
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:29,040
Our order was born
in medeival times

90
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:31,140
and over the centuries
we have created strategies

91
00:05:31,140 --> 00:05:33,100
that have been refined
far beyond anything

92
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:35,110
you rice eaters
could develop.

93
00:05:35,110 --> 00:05:36,240
Our ideas were
battle-tested

94
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:38,090
under so many
different conditions

95
00:05:38,090 --> 00:05:39,240
it boggles the mind

96
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:41,290
and our individual
skills are superior

97
00:05:41,290 --> 00:05:44,220
to your inferior
knowledge of combat.

98
00:05:44,220 --> 00:05:48,130
Your people
know nothing!

99
00:05:48,130 --> 00:05:50,090
This is the end.

100
00:05:50,090 --> 00:05:53,050
Your crude attempts must
be eliminated permanently.

101
00:05:53,050 --> 00:05:55,080
The way you monkey
people use your swords

102
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:57,120
is an abomination to us.

103
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:59,150
You have fought well
against my Lentz,

104
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:01,290
I will try to make
your death painless.

105
00:06:01,290 --> 00:06:03,070
Have you had your say?

106
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:04,110
Even with all that talk,

107
00:06:04,110 --> 00:06:06,140
I'll make this
painless for you.

108
00:06:06,140 --> 00:06:09,250
You are dead!

109
00:06:09,250 --> 00:06:11,150
From the front?

110
00:06:11,150 --> 00:06:12,160
Don't do it!

111
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,050
Kenshin!

112
00:06:14,050 --> 00:06:15,100
Mitsurugi!

113
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:25,110
♪

114
00:06:25,110 --> 00:06:26,110
He did it!

115
00:06:26,110 --> 00:06:27,160
That was fantastic!

116
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:29,050
Great job!

117
00:06:29,050 --> 00:06:30,080
Yoshi was right.

118
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:32,280
Looks like Kuzurysen got
him close enough to strike.

119
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:36,000
Looks like Kenshin's
blow has taken its toll.

120
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:39,110
How did he do that?

121
00:06:39,110 --> 00:06:40,190
(groaning)

122
00:06:40,190 --> 00:06:44,120
Why didn't I take
him more serious?

123
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:46,030
♪

124
00:06:46,030 --> 00:06:47,250
(groaning)

125
00:06:47,250 --> 00:06:50,190
(laughing evilly)

126
00:06:50,190 --> 00:06:52,180
Well, that was
quite a test!

127
00:06:52,180 --> 00:06:57,010
♪

128
00:06:57,010 --> 00:07:00,220
(snickering)

129
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:02,070
He's not even hurt!

130
00:07:02,070 --> 00:07:05,280
♪

131
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:07,240
You know what
you fight like?

132
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,290
A blind baboon!

133
00:07:08,290 --> 00:07:13,000
♪

134
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:16,220
Now you die!

135
00:07:16,220 --> 00:07:18,090
(yells)

136
00:07:18,090 --> 00:07:22,260
♪

137
00:07:22,260 --> 00:07:23,260
(laughing)

138
00:07:23,260 --> 00:07:25,000
He's barely
surviving against

139
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,290
the superiority
of a Black Knight.

140
00:07:26,290 --> 00:07:28,260
Is that the way
of the samurai?

141
00:07:28,260 --> 00:07:30,240
You know nothing!

142
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:34,020
Look how pathetic he is.

143
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:35,150
(grunting)

144
00:07:35,150 --> 00:07:42,160
♪

145
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:44,190
Hmm?

146
00:07:44,190 --> 00:07:46,180
What's he doing?

147
00:07:46,180 --> 00:07:49,100
Oh no!

148
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:52,000
Huh?

149
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,130
The medicine
will be destroyed.

150
00:07:54,130 --> 00:07:57,070
What?

151
00:07:57,070 --> 00:07:59,160
(horse neighs)

152
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:01,110
Lentz, move it!

153
00:08:01,110 --> 00:08:02,270
Lentz, get over here.

154
00:08:02,270 --> 00:08:05,250
I need some of these plants
collected for chemical analysis.

155
00:08:05,250 --> 00:08:08,220
Move it!

156
00:08:08,220 --> 00:08:10,160
We have to put
out the fire.

157
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:12,120
Misanagi, you can't,
you're hurt.

158
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,240
Besides, in a
matter of seconds,

159
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:16,080
that fire will hit the
oil reserves and explode.

160
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:23,240
Yutaro!

161
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:25,030
You want to show
off or something?

162
00:08:25,030 --> 00:08:26,050
Stop that!

163
00:08:26,050 --> 00:08:27,140
Yoshi!

164
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:28,250
What are
they thinking?

165
00:08:28,250 --> 00:08:30,200
I'll get 'em!

166
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:32,150
But Sano, please wait!

167
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:38,290
You must wonder why
I keep toying with you.

168
00:08:38,290 --> 00:08:41,240
I wanted to see you beg.

169
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:43,010
But that's enough.

170
00:08:43,010 --> 00:08:46,210
Now it's time to
finish you off.

171
00:08:46,210 --> 00:08:47,200
(yells)

172
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:55,130
I wasn't able to kill you the
last time I had the chance.

173
00:08:55,130 --> 00:08:57,270
This time you will die
slowly and painfully.

174
00:08:57,270 --> 00:09:00,060
I don't think so,
you overgrown ass!

175
00:09:00,060 --> 00:09:01,150
(yells)

176
00:09:01,150 --> 00:09:02,200
(shouting)

177
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:04,260
Yoshi!

178
00:09:04,260 --> 00:09:06,030
(gasps)

179
00:09:06,030 --> 00:09:09,110
♪

180
00:09:09,110 --> 00:09:11,180
Why is he taking
that stance?

181
00:09:11,180 --> 00:09:15,170
That's the stance used for
Amakakeru Ryu no Hirameki.

182
00:09:15,170 --> 00:09:18,200
But how could his sword move
fast enough for it to work?

183
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,120
Kenshin's lost a
lot of strength.

184
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:22,000
With Meldars
so high on that horse,

185
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,100
I can't understand
Kenshin's thinking.

186
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:25,180
Just let him live.

187
00:09:25,180 --> 00:09:34,120
♪

188
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,170
(urges horse)

189
00:09:35,170 --> 00:09:38,230
♪

190
00:09:38,230 --> 00:09:40,050
(grunts)

191
00:09:40,050 --> 00:09:51,180
♪

192
00:09:51,180 --> 00:09:52,150
(snickers)

193
00:09:54,210 --> 00:09:56,240
Oh no!

194
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:59,030
(shudders)

195
00:09:59,030 --> 00:10:02,070
♪

196
00:10:02,070 --> 00:10:04,150
Against me, I knew even
Japan's greatest would fail.

197
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:06,230
Cause you're all
just monkeys, huh?

198
00:10:06,230 --> 00:10:08,030
Whoa!

199
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:11,110
What the hell?

200
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:13,260
(yelling)

201
00:10:13,260 --> 00:10:15,130
Kenshin beat Meldars.

202
00:10:15,130 --> 00:10:17,040
He chose not to beat
him with his sword,

203
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:19,230
but with his
brains instead.

204
00:10:19,230 --> 00:10:21,190
Meldars was convinced that
he could only be beaten

205
00:10:21,190 --> 00:10:24,190
with a samurai sword.

206
00:10:24,190 --> 00:10:27,060
Kenshin created a vacuum
with his sword's movement

207
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:29,060
and he made sure that fire
would fill that vacuum

208
00:10:29,060 --> 00:10:30,160
right where
Meldars stopped.

209
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:33,160
♪

210
00:10:36,070 --> 00:10:44,250
♪

211
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:46,160
Kenshin!

212
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:48,130
Please, Kenshin, be alive.

213
00:10:48,130 --> 00:10:50,110
Now, you both will die!

214
00:10:50,110 --> 00:10:52,240
(grunts)

215
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:54,070
Now the fun begins.

216
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:56,230
I look forward to
cutting off your arms

217
00:10:56,230 --> 00:10:58,190
and lopping off your
feet might be appropriate

218
00:10:58,190 --> 00:11:01,160
so you won't be able to run
away from the pain and agony.

219
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:04,130
I want to kill you
and all your people.

220
00:11:04,130 --> 00:11:06,100
And you call
yourself a knight?

221
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,180
Huh?

222
00:11:07,180 --> 00:11:10,130
You are the lowest
scum on Earth.

223
00:11:10,130 --> 00:11:13,100
You must be
exterminated.

224
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:16,000
(growls)

225
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,210
You must die first!

226
00:11:17,210 --> 00:11:19,290
(grunts)

227
00:11:23,030 --> 00:11:26,200
(groans)

228
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:28,030
It looks like
you killed him.

229
00:11:28,030 --> 00:11:30,290
I had to, there's no
honor in extermination

230
00:11:30,290 --> 00:11:33,240
but a hatemonger
should be annihilated.

231
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:35,130
Wow!

232
00:11:35,130 --> 00:11:38,160
What the heck
was that explosion?

233
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:40,280
The fire's finally reached
some of the oil reserves.

234
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:42,180
That's the end
of the medicine.

235
00:11:42,180 --> 00:11:45,230
We better get everyone out
of here or we'll be killed.

236
00:11:45,230 --> 00:11:47,120
♪

237
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:48,140
Hmm.

238
00:11:48,140 --> 00:11:50,030
-Yoshi.
-Huh?

239
00:11:50,030 --> 00:11:51,030
Hold my sword.

240
00:11:51,030 --> 00:11:52,140
-Wha-- wait!
-Yutaro!

241
00:11:52,140 --> 00:11:53,230
-Don't!
-Stop!

242
00:11:53,230 --> 00:11:55,250
Yoshi.

243
00:11:55,250 --> 00:11:57,000
Why'd he run
into the fire?

244
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:58,200
To get the
miracle medicine.

245
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,200
What?

246
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,230
Why'd he do
something like that?

247
00:12:00,230 --> 00:12:02,010
He'll get killed.

248
00:12:02,010 --> 00:12:04,070
Damn it,
I'm going after him.

249
00:12:04,070 --> 00:12:07,070
You stay here and gather up
Kaoru and your other friends.

250
00:12:07,070 --> 00:12:12,010
♪

251
00:12:12,010 --> 00:12:13,120
All three of them.

252
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,180
I hope they live.

253
00:12:14,180 --> 00:12:15,290
You have
got to believe.

254
00:12:15,290 --> 00:12:17,050
Sano will rescue them.

255
00:12:17,050 --> 00:12:23,160
♪

256
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:25,020
(grunting)

257
00:12:25,020 --> 00:12:33,240
♪

258
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,000
I think we better leave.

259
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,270
It's too dangerous.

260
00:12:36,270 --> 00:12:38,290
I think I'll stay here.

261
00:12:38,290 --> 00:12:42,130
Everything that I believed could
help us has been destroyed.

262
00:12:42,130 --> 00:12:44,280
It's gone,
it's all in shambles.

263
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:46,080
I'm sorry.

264
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:47,130
I'm partly to
blame for taking

265
00:12:47,130 --> 00:12:49,140
so much away
from you, Misanagi,

266
00:12:49,140 --> 00:12:52,040
but once I really
knew you, I changed.

267
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:53,190
I want to help you.

268
00:12:53,190 --> 00:12:55,230
Our ancestors were
the same kind of people,

269
00:12:55,230 --> 00:12:57,280
fiercely dedicated
to their causes,

270
00:12:57,280 --> 00:13:00,050
but the Black Knight
motives are twisted.

271
00:13:00,050 --> 00:13:01,200
I see that now.

272
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:03,260
Please forgive me
for ever hurting you.

273
00:13:03,260 --> 00:13:05,080
You don't have
to apologize.

274
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,220
When it comes
to this situation,

275
00:13:06,220 --> 00:13:08,210
we've all made mistakes.

276
00:13:08,210 --> 00:13:10,000
I thank you.

277
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:13,020
I'm grateful you chose to save
my life, but now it's over.

278
00:13:13,020 --> 00:13:15,070
One setback
and you give up?

279
00:13:15,070 --> 00:13:17,200
Life's more precious
than that, Misanagi,

280
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:19,240
don't just throw us away.

281
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:21,130
Wait, what do you mean "us"?

282
00:13:21,130 --> 00:13:23,130
You've been saying that your
life's not worth living.

283
00:13:23,130 --> 00:13:24,170
Well, you're wrong.

284
00:13:24,170 --> 00:13:26,090
I have risked my
own life to save you.

285
00:13:26,090 --> 00:13:28,160
I would not put my life
on the line for anyone

286
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:30,080
I did not feel
was important.

287
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:32,030
Doesn't that
mean something?

288
00:13:32,030 --> 00:13:34,270
To give up on your life now,
is to do a disservice to me

289
00:13:34,270 --> 00:13:36,200
and to your ancestors as well.

290
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:38,030
Don't give up on life.

291
00:13:38,030 --> 00:13:40,190
Besides, you and I
still have so much to do.

292
00:13:40,190 --> 00:13:42,100
That's right!

293
00:13:42,100 --> 00:13:43,180
Kaita!

294
00:13:43,180 --> 00:13:56,070
♪

295
00:13:56,070 --> 00:13:58,190
(breathing heavily)

296
00:13:58,190 --> 00:14:02,170
♪

297
00:14:02,170 --> 00:14:03,270
Huh?

298
00:14:03,270 --> 00:14:07,030
♪

299
00:14:07,030 --> 00:14:09,000
Lieutenant Meldars!

300
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:13,110
♪

301
00:14:13,110 --> 00:14:15,190
Lieutenant!

302
00:14:15,190 --> 00:14:21,080
♪

303
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:22,260
(gasps)

304
00:14:22,260 --> 00:14:24,180
♪

305
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:25,230
It's gone.

306
00:14:25,230 --> 00:14:28,080
My master plan
went up in smoke

307
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:30,170
and I'm the one
who lit the fire.

308
00:14:30,170 --> 00:14:33,130
All I have left
is nothing but ashes.

309
00:14:33,130 --> 00:14:36,170
(laughing maniacally)

310
00:14:36,170 --> 00:14:38,220
♪

311
00:14:38,220 --> 00:14:41,140
No, don't go!

312
00:14:41,140 --> 00:14:43,230
Schneider!

313
00:14:43,230 --> 00:14:45,000
Go.

314
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Leave this
hell and live.

315
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:51,040
I love you!

316
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:52,230
Misanagi!

317
00:14:52,230 --> 00:14:58,280
♪

318
00:14:58,280 --> 00:15:00,130
Why?

319
00:15:00,130 --> 00:15:10,180
♪

320
00:15:10,180 --> 00:15:14,100
(grunting softly)

321
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:15,130
Where-- where is it?

322
00:15:15,130 --> 00:15:17,160
Yutaro!

323
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:19,280
There's no use in you
taking anymore chances here.

324
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:21,170
So much of your life
is still ahead of you.

325
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:24,020
You can't become a doctor
if you don't stay alive.

326
00:15:24,020 --> 00:15:26,010
I believe in you
and your future.

327
00:15:26,010 --> 00:15:28,020
Now, let's get going.

328
00:15:28,020 --> 00:15:30,290
Boy, it sure is a neat feeling
when people believe in you.

329
00:15:30,290 --> 00:15:32,260
Now, I know what it feels
like to be a birthday cake

330
00:15:32,260 --> 00:15:34,280
baking in an oven,
but let's put that idea

331
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:36,060
on the backburner for now.

332
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:37,080
Now, what are
we going to do?

333
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:38,180
(horse neighs)

334
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:39,250
Hmm?

335
00:15:39,250 --> 00:15:41,030
(horse whinnies)

336
00:15:45,270 --> 00:15:49,250
I can't believe Yutaro left his
most prized possession with me.

337
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:52,020
Maybe I should
have been nicer to him.

338
00:15:52,020 --> 00:15:53,090
Huh?

339
00:15:53,090 --> 00:15:56,040
♪

340
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:59,030
Six-five Sanosuke
saves the day.

341
00:15:59,030 --> 00:16:01,030
It's all right,
I came back, Yoshi!

342
00:16:01,030 --> 00:16:04,000
Why are you making such a
big deal about it, Yutaro?

343
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:05,150
It sure took
you two long enough

344
00:16:05,150 --> 00:16:07,180
to figure out how
to get back here.

345
00:16:21,070 --> 00:16:23,230
So, I'd say we found out
that samurais like Kenshin

346
00:16:23,230 --> 00:16:25,170
are not to be trifled with.

347
00:16:25,170 --> 00:16:27,270
We saw the bushido style
for fighting works.

348
00:16:27,270 --> 00:16:29,170
Pretty impressive, eh Lentz?

349
00:16:29,170 --> 00:16:32,110
(groans)

350
00:16:41,070 --> 00:16:44,210
♪

351
00:16:44,210 --> 00:16:46,250
I thought that unifying
our Sanada ninja group

352
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:48,140
with the Black Knights
would help us,

353
00:16:48,140 --> 00:16:49,240
but these
creatures from Europe

354
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:51,020
have no sense of honor.

355
00:16:51,020 --> 00:16:54,050
They failed and broke the
promises they made to us.

356
00:16:54,050 --> 00:16:56,270
Not only did they fail,
I failed as well.

357
00:16:56,270 --> 00:16:59,100
I was vigilant about
the Black Knights actions,

358
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:01,090
but the great gift
our ancestors left us,

359
00:17:01,090 --> 00:17:03,290
the holy medicine,
was destroyed.

360
00:17:03,290 --> 00:17:05,200
I'm willing to
accept any punishment

361
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:07,180
the group sees
fit to give me.

362
00:17:07,180 --> 00:17:09,100
That is enough, Misanagi.

363
00:17:09,100 --> 00:17:10,220
You did everything
that you could

364
00:17:10,220 --> 00:17:13,000
to further the goals
of our Sanada group.

365
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,240
What happened was
beyond your control.

366
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:17,290
I know it!

367
00:17:17,290 --> 00:17:19,020
But I--

368
00:17:19,020 --> 00:17:20,290
I believe that
Kaita is right.

369
00:17:20,290 --> 00:17:22,220
We know our group's power
has been declining

370
00:17:22,220 --> 00:17:24,230
since the end
of the Tokugawa era.

371
00:17:24,230 --> 00:17:27,180
We also knew it was a risk to
align ourself with foreigners,

372
00:17:27,180 --> 00:17:30,050
but now is the time we
really need to pull together.

373
00:17:30,050 --> 00:17:32,270
With our strength united,
we will stand tall.

374
00:17:32,270 --> 00:17:34,060
Chara speaks the truth!

375
00:17:34,060 --> 00:17:36,200
Yes, Misanagi
should be our leader!

376
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:38,160
We must make
our group stronger

377
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:40,200
and Misanagi is
a brave leader!

378
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:43,070
Besides, she's better
looking than any of you.

379
00:17:43,070 --> 00:17:45,040
(laughing)

380
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:47,270
That's an insult considering
the way you look, Soricho.

381
00:17:47,270 --> 00:17:51,080
Well, you're not exactly a
wood carving yourself, Rachiro.

382
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:53,220
(group all laughing)

383
00:17:53,220 --> 00:17:57,110
♪

384
00:17:57,110 --> 00:17:59,200
(crying)

385
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:02,040
Schneider,
you saved my life.

386
00:18:02,040 --> 00:18:04,170
You told me not to
give up on my dreams.

387
00:18:04,170 --> 00:18:05,220
I only wish you were here,

388
00:18:05,220 --> 00:18:07,140
so I could share
my love with you.

389
00:18:07,140 --> 00:18:12,090
♪

390
00:18:14,010 --> 00:18:18,170
(groaning)

391
00:18:18,170 --> 00:18:20,060
Sano, he's conscious!

392
00:18:20,060 --> 00:18:21,160
Really, he is?

393
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:23,050
I'd better get Megumi!

394
00:18:23,050 --> 00:18:24,210
♪

395
00:18:24,210 --> 00:18:27,210
Huh, so you're saying this
little plant saved my life?

396
00:18:27,210 --> 00:18:29,120
I used an extract
from that root

397
00:18:29,120 --> 00:18:33,210
to save you from wounds
that should have killed you.

398
00:18:33,210 --> 00:18:35,090
So, that means...

399
00:18:35,090 --> 00:18:37,130
This is it!

400
00:18:37,130 --> 00:18:38,170
The holy medicine.

401
00:18:38,170 --> 00:18:39,180
Mm-hmm.

402
00:18:39,180 --> 00:18:40,200
That is it.

403
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:42,230
That root is from a
flowering plant we found.

404
00:18:42,230 --> 00:18:46,040
It's the miracle medicine
we've dreamed and talked of.

405
00:18:46,040 --> 00:18:48,020
It really is a
miracle medicine.

406
00:18:48,020 --> 00:18:50,150
With the wounds you had,
you really had no chance.

407
00:18:50,150 --> 00:18:52,010
Your breathing and
pulse were so low,

408
00:18:52,010 --> 00:18:53,270
I thought within
minutes you'd be dead,

409
00:18:53,270 --> 00:18:55,170
but that extract
stabilized you

410
00:18:55,170 --> 00:18:57,180
and your recovery's
been unbelievable.

411
00:18:57,180 --> 00:18:59,180
Hey, Dr. Hans,
there's a letter for you

412
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:01,000
from the German consulate.

413
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:05,190
♪

414
00:19:05,190 --> 00:19:07,010
It says that Lentz
and Schneider,

415
00:19:07,010 --> 00:19:08,170
the last two members
of the Black Knights,

416
00:19:08,170 --> 00:19:09,250
have been found.

417
00:19:09,250 --> 00:19:12,110
They turned themselves
in to the authorities,

418
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:13,200
but that's not all.

419
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:15,060
They plan on going
back to Germany

420
00:19:15,060 --> 00:19:17,190
and dismantling the
rest of the Black Knights.

421
00:19:17,190 --> 00:19:19,260
This really signals the
end of the Black Knights.

422
00:19:19,260 --> 00:19:21,090
So, it's safe to
go back to Germany?

423
00:19:21,090 --> 00:19:22,090
Mm-hmm.

424
00:19:22,090 --> 00:19:33,140
♪

425
00:19:33,140 --> 00:19:36,230
It's hard to imagine I may
never see this dojo again.

426
00:19:36,230 --> 00:19:38,130
I learned so much here.

427
00:19:38,130 --> 00:19:41,220
Not just about fighting, but
about how to live life as well.

428
00:19:41,220 --> 00:19:58,280
♪

429
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:02,120
(yelling)

430
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:04,130
♪

431
00:20:04,130 --> 00:20:08,020
Try again and keep
your feet facing forward.

432
00:20:08,020 --> 00:20:10,040
(yelling)

433
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:14,170
♪

434
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:20,030
He was standing there alone?

435
00:20:20,030 --> 00:20:23,190
I guess Yutaro's really
gonna miss being here.

436
00:20:23,190 --> 00:20:25,220
We should do
something nice for him.

437
00:20:25,220 --> 00:20:27,160
After all, he's
really a great kid.

438
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:29,240
Let's give him a
special going away gift.

439
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:32,030
I think I know exactly
what he would like to have.

440
00:20:37,110 --> 00:20:39,190
(ship's horn blows)

441
00:20:39,190 --> 00:20:41,190
I just can't see
you quitting kendo!

442
00:20:41,190 --> 00:20:43,260
You'd better not!

443
00:20:43,260 --> 00:20:45,170
Take it easy, Yoshi.

444
00:20:45,170 --> 00:20:48,180
Yutaro's chosen to continue
studying medicine instead.

445
00:20:48,180 --> 00:20:50,040
He must follow his heart.

446
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:52,020
Right, a hunter
who chases two rabbits

447
00:20:52,020 --> 00:20:54,050
winds up with
nothing for dinner.

448
00:20:54,050 --> 00:20:56,040
We all wish you
lots of luck.

449
00:20:56,040 --> 00:20:59,010
But we wanted you to have this
special gift from us, Yutaro.

450
00:20:59,010 --> 00:21:00,240
The Kamiya Kasshin
spirit will assist you

451
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:02,130
in your studies
of medicine.

452
00:21:02,130 --> 00:21:04,130
I'm letting you
off easy, buddy,

453
00:21:04,130 --> 00:21:06,140
but if you don't live with
the spirit of Kamiya Kasshin,

454
00:21:06,140 --> 00:21:08,070
I swear, I'll
come over there.

455
00:21:08,070 --> 00:21:09,160
You understand me?

456
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:10,180
Understood.

457
00:21:10,180 --> 00:21:13,000
I'll be the first
Kasshin doctor.

458
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,150
All right!

459
00:21:14,150 --> 00:21:15,220
And we'll compete
to see which one

460
00:21:15,220 --> 00:21:17,120
becomes the best
in his field.

461
00:21:17,120 --> 00:21:18,140
Okay?

462
00:21:18,140 --> 00:21:20,150
You bet,
and I'll win.

463
00:21:20,150 --> 00:21:25,290
♪

464
00:21:25,290 --> 00:21:26,290
Miss Kaoru?

465
00:21:26,290 --> 00:21:28,200
What, Kenshin?

466
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:30,170
With Yutaro and
Yoshi as students,

467
00:21:30,170 --> 00:21:33,170
your Kamiya Kasshin style
has a bright future.

468
00:21:33,170 --> 00:21:35,260
(ship's horn blows)

469
00:21:35,260 --> 00:21:43,170
♪

470
00:21:43,170 --> 00:21:45,030
You are a lucky
young man, Yutaro.

471
00:21:45,030 --> 00:21:47,200
You have many friends.

472
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,290
Huh?

473
00:21:48,290 --> 00:21:50,160
I'm a very
lucky man as well,

474
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:51,260
because I have a
bright, disciplined,

475
00:21:51,260 --> 00:21:53,150
young man as my protege.

476
00:21:53,150 --> 00:21:55,140
You, Yutaro.

477
00:21:55,140 --> 00:21:58,200
Thank you, sir, I appreciate
your praise, Dr. Hans.

478
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:01,080
Yes, someday, the
world will be proud of you.

479
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:03,220
♪

480
00:22:03,220 --> 00:22:05,280
Yutaro, if you
want to be great,

481
00:22:05,280 --> 00:22:08,250
then dedicate yourself
to always doing your best.

482
00:22:08,250 --> 00:22:10,020
I-- I promise.

483
00:22:10,020 --> 00:22:11,070
That's the spirit.

484
00:22:11,070 --> 00:22:14,120
Being with those friends
has made you even stronger.

485
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:16,050
You're right, they
gave me love and respect

486
00:22:16,050 --> 00:22:17,190
that I will
remember always.

487
00:22:17,190 --> 00:22:21,070
♪

488
00:22:21,070 --> 00:22:23,280
I thank my good friends
at the Kamiya dojo.

489
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:27,240
Sanosuke, Kaoru,
Yoshi, Misao,

490
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:29,190
my deepest
thanks go to you,

491
00:22:29,190 --> 00:22:32,130
and most of all,

492
00:22:32,130 --> 00:22:33,240
thanks Kenshin.

493
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:38,150
♪

494
00:22:40,622 --> 00:25:02,290
♪

495
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:06,280
♪

